  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the study is to compare home-based aerobic interval training with supervised
      interval training performed in groups or on a treadmill at the hospital.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Cardiac rehabilitation is usually first offered in hospitals, but there are several studies
      that show that home-based rehabilitation is equally efficient. How this comes out when
      exercise is organized as aerobic interval training is not known.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
